description: Sliced Italian Prosciutto is a popular and delicious cured meat that originated in Italy. It is made from the hind leg of the pig, which is dry-cured and aged for several months to develop its unique flavor and texture. The process of making prosciutto involves salting and air-drying the meat, which results in a lean and tender texture that is slightly salty and savory. Sliced Italian Prosciutto is typically served thinly sliced, and can be enjoyed on its own or used as a topping for pizza, salads, sandwiches, and other dishes.
name: Sliced Prosciutto Italiano Import

description: Prosciutto di Parma, a premium quality Italian cured ham that is renowned for its delicate and savory flavor. This exquisite ham is made from the hind legs of specially bred and raised pigs, and has been aged for at least 14 months to develop its unique flavor. Prosciutto di Parma has a beautiful pink color and a sweet aroma that is reminiscent of the Italian countryside. It has a rich and buttery texture that melts in your mouth, with a delicate and savory flavor that is perfect for a variety of dishes. Prosciutto di Parma is a versatile ingredient that can be used in many ways. It is perfect for wrapping around melon, figs, or other fruits, as well as for adding to sandwiches, pizzas, and salads. It can also be enjoyed on its own as a delicious appetizer.
name: 14 Month Prosciutto Italiano

description: Fra' Mani Handcrafted Salumi's Classic Mortadella is made with prime cuts from the leg, shoulder, and belly, carefully trimmed by hand. Minutely fine-ground, with no artificial additives. Speckled with small cubes of pork jowl, the firmest and most flavorful fat on the hog. Slow-roasted for 10 hours with dry heat and finished with a breath of natural fruitwood smoke. description: The King of Italian dry cured hams, Prosciutto di Parma is a highly controlled product, produced under strict Italian law which governs the size of leg to be used, where the legs come from, and what the hogs eat, among other strict considerations. Once the leg has been selected, it undergoes a salting stage that last for a few weeks. Next it is cleaned off to begin the curing process, which occurs in humidity and temperature controlled rooms replicating the fall, winter and spring seasons. This slow process is closely monitored to ensure that the legs are properly cured and that the end product measures up to the high standards established by Italian law.
name: 16 Month Prosciutto di Parma DOP

Enjoy in a classic Spanish paella or in refreshing salad with sweet potato and avocado.

description: Creminelli Salame Finocchiona is a type of Italian salami that is made with high-quality pork meat, spices, and fennel seeds. It has a distinctive flavor and aroma that is both savory and slightly sweet, with a mild level of spiciness. Creminelli Salame Finocchiona is prepared using traditional Italian methods and is naturally aged for several weeks to develop its unique taste and texture. It is a versatile ingredient that can be enjoyed on its own as a snack, or used as a topping for pizzas, sandwiches, and antipasti platters.
name: Fennel Finocchiona Salami

description: This Sopressata is an authentic bite of Northern Italy’s exquisitely rich culinary history. This salame begins with only the finest humanely-raised and 100% vegetarian fed pork, never treated with artificial growth hormones or antibiotics. Rough cuts of meat are blended together for an ideal fat content, while cloves add a wonderfully warm flavor with buttery undertones. Free from nitrates and nitrites, this salame is hand-tied, protected by a natural casing, and dry-aged for about 90 days for the quality you’d expect from true meat maestros. Enjoy atop a crispy piece of grilled bread with a smear of stracciatella for a perfectly indulgent appetizer.
name: Sopressata

description: Sopressata is the most well known of the Italian salamis and the most likely to be familiar even to the uninitiated. The Creminelli Sopressata is redolent of garlic and red wine giving it a robust and easy-to-enjoy flavor. Sopressata, also called Sopressa Veneta, got its name from the practice of pressing the salami between planks of wood resulting in a straight, flattened shape. The northern Italian version from Vicenza, in the Veneto region, did away with the pressed shape and has become an international favorite. Creminelli Sopressata is stuffed into a straight natural casing, hand-tied and then slowly cured.
name: Soppressata Salami

description: This sliced pepperoni packs a flavorful bite of the Old World Italian tradition. Made from only the freshest meats and seasonings, this pepperoni is left to dry for a long two-week period to allow a complex harmony of flavors to develop. This pepperoni is sliced while still enclosed in its collagen casing, causing slight shrink and browned, cupped edges when heated. With no fillers and a delightfully lean texture, this pepperoni is a perfect match for pizza, calzones, and stromboli.

description: Creminelli Tartufo Salami is a gourmet cured meat that offers a unique and savory flavor experience. Made with high-quality pork that is sourced from small family farms, this salami is seasoned with black summer truffles, which adds a rich and earthy flavor to the meat. The salami is slow-cured and naturally fermented, which gives it a tender and succulent texture. The outside of the salami is coated with a layer of white mold, which is a natural byproduct of the curing process and is completely safe to eat. Creminelli Tartufo Salami is perfect as a snack or appetizer, and can be enjoyed on its own or paired with other meats, cheeses, and crackers. It also makes a great addition to sandwiches, pizzas, and charcuterie boards.
name: Truffle Salami

description: This exquisite 16 Month Red Prosciutto Parma begins with 100% Italian pigs and Galloni’s rich tradition for the utmost quality. The meat is hand-salted by experienced masters and then left to mature, where after six months it is smeared with pork fat, pepper, and rice flour for an undeniably delicate texture. A longer maturation period then begins, during which the winds blowing from the Marino sea enter the cellars through vast windows. The prosciutto is then needle sampled with horse shank bone for a precise test of aroma development. The result is a soft, succulent meat with an ideal confluence of white fat and lean meat, boasting a complex salty-sweet flavor profile. Enjoy as a decadent addition to carbonara or combine with melon for a juicy, refreshing amuse-bouche.
name: 16 Month Red Prosciutto di Parma DOP

description: A cured D.O.P. ham made in San Daniele, Friuli, a town in the middle of a plain protected by the Alps to the north and facing the Mediterranean Sea to the south. The climate, the resinous mountain air and the salty scent of the sea give this prosciutto a special flavor, mildness and fragrance like none other. Prosciutto here is made from pigs raised and butchered in Italy without added preservatives or additives and are highly digestible and nourishing.
name: 16 Month Prosciutto San Daniele DOP

description: This exquisite 24 Month Prosciutto Parma begins with 100% Italian pigs and Galloni’s rich tradition for the utmost quality. The meat is hand-salted by experienced masters and then left to mature, where after six months it is smeared with pork fat, pepper, and rice flour for an undeniably delicate texture. A longer maturation period then begins, during which the winds blowing from the Marino sea enter the cellars through vast windows. The prosciutto is then needle sampled with horse shank bone for a precise test of aroma development. The result is a soft, succulent meat with a complex salty-sweet flavor profile. Enjoy as a decadent pizza topping or use to wrap asparagus for a delicious grilled amuse-bouche.
name: 24 Month Prosciutto di Parma DOP

description: Creminelli wild boar salami is a cured meat product made from high-quality wild boar meat. The salami is handcrafted in the traditional Italian style, using a time-honored curing process that results in a rich, complex flavor and a distinctive aroma. The wild boar used in Creminelli salami is sourced from free-range animals that have been allowed to graze and forage in the wild, resulting in a leaner and more flavorful meat. The meat is carefully seasoned with a blend of herbs and spices, including black pepper, fennel, and red wine, and then cured for several weeks to develop its unique flavor.
name: Wild Boar Salami

description: Leoncini Prosciutto Cotto, a premium quality deli meat that is perfect for adding a savory and smoky flavor to your dishes. This exquisite ham is made from high-quality pork that is cooked slowly with aromatic herbs and spices, creating a delicious and satisfying taste. Leoncini Prosciutto Cotto has a beautiful pinkish color and a rich aroma of smokiness and spices. It has a tender and juicy texture that melts in your mouth, making it perfect for sandwiches, salads, or any dish that requires a rich and flavorful ham. This prosciutto cotto is versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for making classic ham sandwiches, or for using in creative dishes like ham and cheese croissants, ham and potato soup, or ham and mushroom quiche.
name: Prosciutto Cotto

description: This Picante Salametto brings a bite of Spain’s exquisitely rich culinary history. This dry chorizo begins with only the finest humanely-raised and 100% vegetarian fed pork, never treated with artificial growth hormones or antibiotics. Smoked paprika adds a kick of heat and sweetness, while cumin brings a grounding savory undertone. Free from nitrates and nitrites, this chorizo is hand-tied, protected by a natural casing, and dry aged for about 35 days for the quality you’d expect from true meat maestros. description: This Toscano Salami is an authentic bite of picturesque Tuscany’s exquisitely rich culinary history. This salami begins with only the finest humanely-raised and 100% vegetarian fed pork, never treated with artificial growth hormones or antibiotics. Crafted with lean pieces of pork and tender white fat, this salami offers a delicate texture and a wonderfully savory flavor that highlights sea salt, black pepper, and garlic with just a touch of red wine. Enjoy it atop a warm slice of unsalted bread with a generous drizzle of extra virgin olive oil for a truly Tuscan snack!

description:
Considered the best jamón in the world, 5J Cinco Jotas Ibérico de Bellota delivers a one-of-a-kind intense floral, nutty, earthy flavor with a soft texture that melts in your mouth.
What makes it so special starts with the 100% Iberian pigs raised on an acorn diet and 5J Cinco Jotas’ devotion to time-honored traditions. The curing process is extensive, and the jamón is aged for five to seven years for optimal flavor and texture. This product comes pre-sliced to perfection—a labor saver that makes it easy to open and ready to serve as part of a beautiful charcuterie, on top of dishes, or as is enjoyed with a glass of cava as they do in Spain.
name: Pre-sliced Ibérico de Bellota Jamón

description: This Calabrese Salame is an authentic bite of Southern Italy’s exquisitely rich culinary history. This salame begins with only the finest humanely-raised and 100% vegetarian fed pork, never treated with artificial growth hormones or antibiotics. Hot and sweet peperoncino, fennel seed, and chili flakes give this charcuterie favorite a flavor resembling licorice with a slight kick of well-rounded heat. Free from nitrates and nitrites, this salame is hand-tied, protected by a natural casing, and dry-aged for about 35 days for the quality you’d expect from true meat maestros. description: This exquisite 20 Month Prosciutto Parma begins with 100% Italian pigs and Galloni’s rich tradition for the utmost quality. The meat is hand-salted by experienced masters and then left to mature, where after six months it is smeared with pork fat, pepper, and rice flour for an undeniably delicate texture. A longer maturation period then begins, during which the winds blowing from the Marino sea enter the cellars through vast windows. The prosciutto is then needle sampled with horse shank bone for a precise test of aroma development. The result is a soft, succulent meat with a complex salty-sweet flavor profile. Enjoy as a decadent pizza topping or use to wrap asparagus for a delicious grilled amuse-bouche.
name: 20 Month Prosciutto di Parma DOP

description: Known as Salami al Barolo in Italy, it is a meat delicacy that comes from Piemonte, the same place that gave birth to Barolo wine, the Slow Food movement and Creminelli's very own founder, Cristiano Creminelli. Creminelli meats are handmade under the supervision of master artisan, Cristiano Creminelli. It is robust and complex with savory, meaty flavor. description: For a superb addition to any charcuterie board, this Molisana Sopressata Salami brings the Italian tradition in full force. Crafted from heritage-breed, 100% vegetarian-fed pork never treated with antibiotics or growth hormones, this salami offers the kick of whole black peppercorns and the pungent, tangy flavor of garlic. description: Olli Salumeria makes artisanal slow-cured meats based on original 160-year-old family recipes that were handed down to 4th generation Italian Salumiere, Oliviero "Olli" Colmignoli. Their products are made with pork from heritage-breed pigs, pasture raised on family-owned sustainable farms. Good salumi is directly affected by the quality of the pork, and Olli Salumeria goes to great lengths to obtain the best heritage-breed (Berkshire and Mangalitsa) pigs available in the USA. The pigs are humanely pasture-raised on family farms (never confined to pens or crates) and are fed all-vegetarian feeds (antibiotic-free and never fed animal by-products). The pigs are grown to mature age and weight for increased flavor (about 8 months vs. industry standard 5-6 months). -old family recipes that were handed down over four generations to our founder.
name: Applewood Smoke Napoli Salami

description: Schaller & Weber New York Style Pastrami is a harmonious blend of top-quality beef, a proprietary spice rub, and a smoking process that imparts a bold, smoky flavor. Each tender, thinly sliced bite is a celebration of savory richness that embodies the essence of New York's deli heritage. We believe in preserving the art of traditional pastrami-making, and our New York Style Pastrami is a testament to that commitment. Each cut is meticulously trimmed, expertly seasoned, and smoked to perfection, embodying the expertise, precision, and authenticity that define Schaller & Weber.  Create classic pastrami sandwiches with all the fixings, add it to gourmet salads, or craft unique appetizers that showcase its bold, smoky flavor.
name: New York City Pastrami

description: Originating in Spain’s southwestern region, this Bone-In Iberico de Bellota is a true savory star. Its delicate texture and touch of sweetness make it a must-have for even the most exquisite of charcuterie boards. Fed a pure acorn diet and never crossbred, each Pata Negra pig is designated two hectares of space to roam. Given similarities in the nutrition profiles of acorns and olive oil, this unique diet has led to the breed’s reputation as “an olive tree with four legs.” Each and every cut is given careful consideration and cured for up to five years, leading to over a century of experience in producing the finest quality ham.
name: Bone-In Iberico de Bellota

description: The King of Italian dry cured hams, Prosciutto di Parma is a highly controlled product, produced under strict Italian law which governs the size of leg to be used, where the legs come from, and what the hogs eat, among other strict considerations. Once the leg has been selected, it undergoes a salting stage that last for a few weeks. Next it is cleaned off to begin the curing process, which occurs in humidity and temperature controlled rooms replicating the fall, winter and spring seasons. This slow process is closely monitored to ensure that the legs are properly cured and that the end product measures up to the high standards established by Italian law.
name: 18 Month Prosciutto di Parma DOP

description: Olympia Provisions Kasekrainer Sausage is a harmonious blend of high-quality pork, smoky bacon, and a decadent pocket of Emmental cheese. Each bite is a burst of savory richness, elevated by the irresistible smokiness of the sausage. We believe in preserving the art of traditional sausage-making, and our Kasekrainer Sausage is a testament to that commitment. It is meticulously crafted in small batches, ensuring that every link is a work of culinary art. We understand that consistency is paramount in the culinary world. Our Kasekrainer Sausage undergoes rigorous quality control measures, ensuring that each sausage meets the highest standards, preserving the flavors and textures that make it exceptional.
name: Kasekrainer Sausage

description: Originating in Spain’s southwestern region, this Iberico Belotta Paleta is a true savory star. Cut from the shoulder, its succulent texture and touch of sweetness make it a must-have for even the most exquisite of charcuterie boards. Fed a pure acorn diet and never crossbred, each Pata Negra pig is designated two hectares of space to roam. Given similarities in the nutrition profiles of acorns and olive oil, this unique diet has led to the breed’s reputation as “an olive tree with four legs.” Each and every cut is given careful consideration and cured for up to five years, leading to over a century of experience in producing the finest quality ham.
name: Iberico Bellota Paleta

description: SPANISH STYLE SPREADABLE SALAMI - Decadent black truffle, spreadable salami. Laced with minced black truffles, sweet Calabrian peppers, and finished with black trufflesalt. ThisuniquerecipeisourversionofthespreadablesalamifromUmbriaknownas Cisco. Umbria is known for producing black truffles, which add depth to this rich salad. Eat on crostoni, or mix into some fresh pasta for a simple, yet luxurious dish! Cremosa Tartufata is our take on the fiasco, the rare delicacy of Umbria, a region renowned for its black truffles. Made with Berkshire pork and sweet Calabrian pepper, we incorporate the highest quality Italian black truffles from Savini to complement this luxurious spreadable salami. Rich and buttery, Cremosa Tartufata is amazing simply tossed with your favorite pasta, or spread over crostini.
name: Cremosa Tartufata Spread

description: Originating in Spain’s southwestern region, this Boneless Iberico de Bellota is a true savory star. Its succulent texture and touch of sweetness make it a must-have for even the most exquisite of charcuterie boards. Fed a pure acorn diet and never crossbred, each Pata Negra pig is designated two hectares of space to roam. Given similarities in the nutrition profiles of acorns and olive oil, this unique diet has led to the breed’s reputation as “an olive tree with four legs.” Each and every cut is given careful consideration and cured for up to five years, leading to over a century of experience in producing the finest quality ham.
name: Boneless Iberico de Bellota

description: This exquisite Bone In Prosciutto Parma begins with 100% Italian pigs and Galloni’s rich tradition for the utmost quality. The meat is hand-salted by experienced masters and then left to mature, where after six months it is smeared with pork fat, pepper, and rice flour for an undeniably delicate texture. A longer maturation period then begins, during which the winds blowing from the Marino sea enter the cellars through vast windows. The prosciutto is then needle sampled with horse shank bone for a precise test of aroma development. The result is a soft, succulent meat with a complex salty-sweet flavor profile. Enjoy as a decadent addition to carbonara or combine with melon for a juicy, refreshing amuse-bouche.
name: Bone In Prosciutto di Parma DOP

description: SPICYUNCUREDPORKCOLLAR-Spicy,dry-agedporkcollar. Thisspicyversionisrubbedwith imported Calabrian chiles, black pepper, juniper berries, and fresh herbs. Aged 4 months. This is a traditional whole-muscle cut that is produced by most salumeria from the collar muscle (shoulder area), and air-dried with precision, similar to prosciutto. Ours has an incredibly deep pork flavor. We use family farm-raised pork, so the animal has an opportunity to use its muscles which adds flavor to the meat. These animals have the unique characteristics of driving flavor deep into each muscle via interlaced intramuscular fat which gives our coppa marbling that exceeds imported or commodity-produced coppa.
name: Uncured Coppa Piccante

description: Lightly Smoky and spiced with peperoncino, paprika and garlic, our pepperoni is slowly aged and air dried, perfect on pizzas or right out of the pack. Pre-sliced this artisan salame comes ready to serve. Add to charcuterie boards, sandwiches, pizzas or simply snack on its own.

description: WAYGU BEEF SALAMI - Salame di Manzo: 100% Wagyu Beef seasoned with Fresh Thyme, Black Pepper, and Cabernet Red Wine compliment the character and unmistakable marbling of premium Wagyu beef.. Manzo, the Italian word for beef is a salame we make from Wagyu beef, including the casing produced from beef collagen. The rich Wagyu meat is enhanced with the addition of thyme, black pepper, and Cabernet wine. Tempesta created Salame di Manzo to bring the authentic flavors of Western European salumi to those who prefer not to eat pork, still, it remains one of our most popular salamis, bringing unique variety to any charcuterie board.
name: Di Manzo Wagyu Salami

description: SPICY BLACK PEPPER SALAMI - Spicy sopressata. Sea salt and Tellicherry black pepper and a kiss of Calabrian chili pepper paste. Madewith Berkshire and Duroc pigs raised on family farms in southern Minnesota, without antibiotics or hormones, and always vegetarian-fed. Piccante, hot, spicy... However you say it, this salad has some sizzle! Calabria made it famous and this is our homage to the Fischer family’s ancestral region. Calabrian peppers lend a balanced heat, and soften high-quality fats giving way to sensual glory on your palate! After a few slices, the slow burn culminates in a pleasurably spicy bite! Pair with Champagne, oysters, and your favorite Marvin Gaye album.
name: Sopressata Piccante

description: FENNEL POLLEN SALAMI - 2016 Good Food Award 2018 sofiTM Gold Award = The best-crafted meat on the American market! Our award-winning Tuscan fennel salami seasoned with fennel seeds, fennel pollen, a hint of garlic and a healthy glug of chianti wine. Made with Heritage Berkshire and Duroc pigs raised on family farms without antibiotics or hormones, and always vegetarian-fed. Finocchiona meaning “fennel salami” is identified closely with the region of Tuscany. We are proud to present our Finocchiona as equal to any version imported from Italy, and frankly, we think ours is better! In fact, in this salami brought us our first sofiTM Gold award, proclaimed in international competition as the best-crafted meat or poultry of any kind! Like authentic salame Tuscano, we complement our Finocchiona with black pepper, Sangiovese wine, a sprinkling of whole fennel seed, and a blast of wild fennel pollen.
name: Finocchiona Fennel Salami
